<br>
Everything I have written below is true to my knowledge, think maybe I should open the eyes of some. I know truth hurts sometimes... I was present at all events... <br>
<br>
Xlabikx how about you read what you write before calling people names.. if anyone here is a hypocrite, it's you. Just take a look at the title of the topic you started, then your reply 1/2 way down the page.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Don't you all Love Hypocrits? I sure as hell love Fotc!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fotc as a whole? I've seen some shady things pulled by you guys, but nothing to put you all onto my hate list, especially with a few close friends/old guildies<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The majority of the time you flame any FotC member you do not use their name. You generalize it to FotC; a FotC group did this or FotC did that. Whether it is 1 person or a raid force, when you say FotC you mean the WHOLE GUILD. And what &quot;shady things&quot; have you seen FotC pull exactly??? For those of you who don't know Xlabikx and FotC have history.. and he no doubt holds a grudge.<br>
<br>
In like March or April, when GoD died, Milon (FotC's GL at the time) was approached by what was left of GoD asking for a merger. We made it quite clear that it was an absorption and that FotC guidelines were to remain in place etc. Anyways like 10 of them tagged over in about a weeks time, Xlab was one of these. After 3 days tagged he made a post on our message boards (some older FotC players may remember it), &quot;<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WTF... Things need to change</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;. In this post he pretty much tore the guild apart in his words. EVERYTHING we did was totally wrong, our raiding system, our DPK system <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(we like to have fun while we give out loot, most people love the system, even though it takes a min or 2 longer than the regular)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> our recruiting system, he also said that our (then) current officers needed to be replaced, the way we talk, the way we walk.. everything you could imagine. The way he saw it, unless we became &quot;Generic_clone_raiding_guild_6045761&quot; then we didn't have a chance. Maybe he mistook our guild forum with the blast furnace?<br>
<br>
He didn't stop there.. he began sending tells to a lot of our members trying to turn them to his cause. He sent tells to members that were to the effect of, &quot;Milon is a complete idiot and he needs to be replaced, this guild will not last long&quot;. I just remember him calling Milon an idiot for sure, it was like a week after I was promoted to officer so it sticks in my mind. Anyways he said 1/2 the guild was with him and they'd quit if Milon remained GL. Milon promptly kicked him out and after a day the majority of the GoD sheep detagged and followed suit, although we did keep a couple good people. No one who had been a member before Xlab/GoD joined followed him. Just ask yourself, is this the sort of person I want in my guild? <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Hell no</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Maybe one day he'll get over the fact that his ass was kicked to the curb, then again he seems pretty stubborn..<br>
<br>
<br>
Hevyd? To be honest I have no idea why you have a problem with FotC, besides the whole &quot;Grend&quot; thing in BoT last week. But you've been gunning for us for months now. I know you had a run in or 2 with Sycik here on the BF.. but pretty much everyone did. He's no longer in our guild or even on this server, yet you still hold a grudge against the entire guild. I did group with you not too long ago, you seemed like a decent guy. A little immature, seemed the whole conversation on /gs was about the size of woodelf breasts.....<br>
<br>
Sorry that this is kind of long, but I want to clarify things for you &quot;viewers&quot;.<br>
<br>
I've seen a few people comment on the whole &quot;<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FotC KS'd Kland from GoL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot; incident...were any of you there? If so, please chime in. I was, let me paint you a picture..<br>
<br>
Both guilds started zoning into WW about the same time and set up near DN zone in, I can't say who had the first person in zone, like it matters. FotC had our members there buffed, ready first and engaged. 10-15 seconds after we engaged we had 2-4 WW dragons add on us (I can't say for sure how many, I died straight away) and obviously we wiped. GoL were very vocal that it wasn't them, that it was some random person going into DN.. and YES we totally took their word for it. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(Sound familiar to anyone? Like the 2 PoZ's that added onto us at 30% left on AoW? Ohh nm maybe we trained ourselves, according to GoL one of our people just ran off and aggro'd them because AoW was just too darn easy and we needed a challenge. --------- <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>No I am not blaming GoL for that</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.. maybe it was just a coincidence, there were a few other people in the zone at the time. Seems being near GoL is bad luck though).</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
K anyway we wiped.. we dragged the corpses out.. we rezzed, rebuffed and med'd to FOM and GoL still hadn't engaged. Milon shouted/ooc'd (I don't remember which), &quot;We do not have all night, we are ready to engage again. You have 5(10? Don't remember exactly) mins to engage or we will.&quot; Milon gave them a count down every minute, &quot;you have 4 mins to engage&quot;, &quot;you have 3 mins to engage&quot;, etc. When there was about 1-2 mins left Huuse /ooc's, &quot;hey guys, what's happening&quot; and the GoL cheer goes up.. &quot;hey Huuse&quot;, etc. Obviously they had been stalling because they didn't have their MT there. At about 1 min I guess they began to coh-debuff, Huuse still wasn't at their camp and I guess they saw it as a way to hold us off. &quot;You have 30 seconds to engage&quot;, then, &quot;ok charge guys&quot;.. and we went in and killed it. To be honest, not all FotC members were ok with this, but how long do you wait??? We could have been there hours ago with a mage and shammy CoH debuffing waiting on the raid to arrive, is that alright???<br>
<br>
The whole AoW thing.. there is one thing I don't understand here. How do guilds think they have ANY right to this mob? If a guild takes the time to kill vindi/statue/idol then they sure as hell deserve AoW, whether they fail or not. If you want AoW, then you get your ass in Kael when statue pops and do the whole sequence and earn it. If a guild wipes, they deserve the 2nd chance, THAT is what pissed off us when GoL took it at 1%. 90% (there is always those who love the loot) of the guild didn't give a shit about the loot.. we were pissed that GoL robbed us of our 2nd attempt! I'm sorry but they didn't have a chance in hell of killing it with the force they had there. Had they not aggro'd it before we wiped, Otana (my RL wife who was FD) would have stayed down to rez a cleric... but she stood to try get the kill, seeing as GoL had engaged before the total wipe. This isn't the first time we've been &quot;taunted by other guilds&quot; .. on our first attempt TWC did it.. on our 2nd ToN (which we won and a storm was bitched up about it), and then GoL who killed it at 1%. At least the first two guilds had class about it. You will never see FotC hovering over a guild like a bunch of vultures.<br>
<br>
We have only tried this guy 3 times.. and every time we've had another guild in zone waiting for us to fail.. Why? What makes you guys actually think you deserve the right to even engage a mob someone else spawns? Going to take SSRA as an example, if I kill R1, R2 and then AL pops, that mob is MINE. If anyone wants to kill it too bad, even if I wipe all day long.. I've taken the time to spawn it, therefore it is mine. Sure if I leave and give up, then whoever wants it can take it.. but until that point stay the hell back.<br>
<br>
BoT .. what a shithole of a zone. From when I've exp'd there, there is usually 2 camps to each wing.. 1 at hub and 1 at the pad for those who don't know (Pad = where named spawn). Daily there are races for named and if you are camped at the pad, well there is no competition. If you are camping the hub, I'm sorry but its my opinion that you are NOT camping that PAD. KS's etc happen daily in BoT .. but the second you see a FotC tag in the mix it's a fucking conspiracy. I'm going to use SSRA again as a reference; there is a group in comm1 and a group in comm2 .. rhag1 pops.. is this automatically comm1's mob, just because they are on the same floor? Even though they need to MOVE to it.. NO it's whoever it is that gets to the mobs room first. If someone calls Rhag1 room before it's popped.. then sure.. it's all yours.. <br>
<br>
As you've all seen, there has been a few complaints about BoT and to be honest not one person has approached me about this. I guess the BF is an easier place to whine. If you have a problem with a member of FotC, contact an officer and it will be dealt with.. not that hard eh? This issue has been confronted on our guild forums, there has even been a guideline of rules concerning BoT formulated and posted.<br>
<br>
I dunno about you other guilds, but in FotC there is a rule that we don't talk shit about other guilds. I guess we'd expect the same of you other guilds, but looking at the BF.. I guess we are alone on that. Of course, it isn't easy to police, but those are the rules. If you break it, then you get a verbal warning. If you repeat it, later. To be honest a lot of the childish people who were in our guild are gone now and in the last month we've been growing into a stronger guild. Our goals are in sight - VT - yeah its a big step.. but we are working hard towards it.. and we will get there or die trying.<br>
<br>
No doubt people are going to come out of the woodwork to flame this post.. but say whetever you want, every word of it is the truth and nothing will change that. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=413678">Shalladiah</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 65 Monk - Guild Leader of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fotcguild.com">Fate of the Chosen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chingerz>chingerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/29/03 10:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3433.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fate of the Chosen</span><hr size=1> Can someone summarize this in a single paragraph for the short attention span crowd? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40574">Chingerz Angsantos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hneguild.com">Heaven and Earth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern">Saryrn</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
