<br>
I agree with most of what you said, with the exception of one point regarding AoW.  He's a highly contested spawn that despawns quickly once triggered if not aggroed.  You have had other guilds shadowing you (including us) on this because there is a reasonable chance that you will fail.  Just because you spawn the mob does not mean you have the right to have him despawn.  Arch Lich is another matter, he doesn't despawn, and as far as I'm concerned, if you want to spend all day in there wiping to him multiple times, feel free.<br>
<br>
